    <lemma xml:id="lem-sheafy-exact-sequence">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Let <m>A</m> be a solid analytic ring. Then for any <m>f,g \in A^{\triangleright}(*)</m> generating the unit ideal, we have an exact sequence
          <men xml:id="eq-sheafy-exact-sequence">
            0 \to A^{\triangleright} \to A\left\langle \tfrac{f}{g} \right\rangle^{\triangleright} \oplus 
            A\left\langle \tfrac{g}{f} \right\rangle^{\triangleright} \to  A\left\langle \tfrac{f}{g}, \tfrac{g}{f} \right\rangle^{\triangleright} \to 0
          </men>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <proof>
        <p>
          By 
          Recall that the derived localizations are represented by the corresponding Koszul complexes (<xref ref="rem-localization-is-underived"/>).
          Apply <xref ref="lem-solid-split-laurent-poly-ring"/> to obtain an exact sequence
          <me>
            0 \to 0 \to A^{\triangleright}[T]_{\liquid T}  \oplus T^{-1} A^{\triangleright}[T^{-1}]_{\liquid T^{-1}} \to A^{\triangleright}[T^{\pm}]_{\liquid T^{\pm}} \to 0
          </me>
          and a split exact sequence
          <me>
            0 \to A^{\triangleright} \to A^{\triangleright}[T]_{\liquid T} \oplus A^{\triangleright}[T^{-1}]_{\liquid T^{-1}} \to A^{\triangleright}[T^{\pm}]_{\liquid T^{\pm}} \to 0
